    "statement": "Let $P$ be the point on the parabola $y^2=4x$ that is at the shortest distance from the centre $S$ of the circle $x^2+y^2-4x-16y+64=0$. Let $Q$ be the point on the circle that divides the line segment $SP$ internally. Then\n\n(A) $SP=2\\sqrt5$ ┬Ę (B) $SQ:QP=(\\sqrt5+1):2$ ┬Ę (C) the $x$-intercept of the normal to the parabola at $P$ is $6$ ┬Ę (D) the slope of the tangent to the circle at $Q$ is $\\dfrac12$",
