          "Here $R$ corresponds to $\\theta=\\tfrac{\\pi}{6}$ and $S$ to $\\theta=\\tfrac{\\pi}{3}$. Immediately $|N_1P|=\\tfrac23|N_1R|$ and $|N_2Q|=\\tfrac23|N_2S|$ ŌĆö the ratio is the fixed constant $b/a=2/3$, independent of the angle. This gives (C): $3|N_2Q|=2|N_2S|$ instantly, and refutes (D): $9|N_1P|=6|N_1R|\\ne 4|N_1R|$.",
          "The ellipse points are then $P=(3\\cos\\tfrac{\\pi}{6},2\\sin\\tfrac{\\pi}{6})=\\left(\\tfrac{3\\sqrt3}{2},1\\right)$ and $Q=(3\\cos\\tfrac{\\pi}{3},2\\sin\\tfrac{\\pi}{3})=\\left(\\tfrac32,\\sqrt3\\right)$.",
